position.}) 17. a4 $16 {1-0 (51) Repanic,F (2082) -Plume,G (2080) ICCF email
2017}) 6. c3 {The idea is to postpone the move Re1, and after d4-d5, the queen
can go to the e2-square.} (6. Re1 Bd7 {This transposes to the Steinitz
variation.}) 6... Nxe4 $5 {There aren't a lot of games with this move, but
lately it has become popular.} (6... b5 7. Bc2 {[%cal Gd2d4] Will transpose
