Re1 Ne5 18. Bf4 f6 19. a4 $1 $18 {[%cal Gd1d5] White wants to open up the
a-file while Black can't castle short due to Qxd5+ with a double attack.}) 15.
b3 Nb6 16. Re1 Qxe7 17. Ba3 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Ga3e7] Pinning the knight.} O-O-O
18. Rxe6 Qxe6 19. Bxc5 $18 {Black can maybe try 19...d4 to complicate matters
a bit where White can simply recapture with 20.cxd4, but in any case, White
has a winning advantage.}) (11... Nxd4 12. cxd4 $16 {[%cal Gf2f4,Gf4f5]}) 12.
Nxe6 Qxe6 (12... fxe6 13. Qh5+ {This check is very unpleasant since Black
needs to move the king.}) (12... Nxe6 13. f4 $16 {White will push f4-f5
eventually.}) 13. b4 Na4 {Black's idea is to sacrifice a pawn and to castle,
but White has no need to give up the strong bishop on c2.} 14. f4 $16 {[%cal
Gd1d3,Gd1h5] After Black castles short, White has ideas like Qd3 or Qh5, with
an attack.}) (10... Qd7 $6 11. Nd4 {Black still can't capture the pawn on e5
due to f2-f4.} Bg4 12. f3 (12. Qd2 $5 {[%cal Gh2h3] Is also playable, with h3
and f4 next.}) 12... Bh5 13. Be3 $16 {[%cal Gb1d2] This is a better version
for White from similar positions which will be discussed later.}) 11. h3 {
